title: m39
speaker: GRETKOV
speech: Bourne comes here? Why?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: He left yesterday on the night train. He's probably just getting in now.  You'll have to hurry.

title: m39
speaker: GRETKOV
speech: What?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Save it for Bourne.

title: m39
speaker: GRETKOV
speech: Go to the airport. Get a plane. I'll have a brass band waiting for you.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: What do you mean?

title: m39
speaker: GRETKOV
speech: Leaving was a business decision. We're both rich come enjoy it.

title: m39
speaker: GRETKOV
speech: One last push. One.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Neski was a roadblock. Without me there's no company no fortune. You owe me Uri. One last push.

title: m39
speaker: GRETKOV
speech: Anything else?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: She's done everything I wanted. She bit on Conklin so fast it was laughable. She even found his bogus Swiss account...

title: m39
speaker: GRETKOV
speech: And the Landy woman?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: No. The files are spotless. Whatever they find it's just going to make Conklin look worse.

title: m39
speaker: GRETKOV
speech: Will it track back to us?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: I'll say. You killed his goddam girlfriend instead. Now they're onto Neski. They're at the Brecker Hotel even as we speak.

title: m39
speaker: GRETKOV
speech: There was a mistake.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: You told me Bourne was dead.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Well you're probably right. I guess that's all that hubris is.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: No. You lost your way.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: In the end honestly it's hubris. Simple hubris. You reach a point in this game when the only satisfaction left is to see how clever you are.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: No good options left?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Had to be done.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: And Danny Zorn what was that?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Why not? It was just money.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: And pocketed a fair amount of change while doing it.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: I'm not a traitor. I've served my ountry.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: 'Why' would be enough for me.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: I don't exactly know what to say -- I'm sorry.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: I'd rather stand if it's all the same to you.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Sit down.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: I'm sorry Ward.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Jesus... I Zorn... I have to call his family. Tell them...

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: Don't know.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Moscow? What the Hell's he going to Moscow for?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: No... It must have been Bourne.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: Did he say anything to you?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Oh God... It must have been Bourne.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: They found Danny Zorn's body. Dead in the basement at the building where my people got hit the first time.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: What?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: I wasn't sleeping.  You OK?

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: Sorry to wake you.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: Well whatever he's doing I've had enough -- this is now a search and destroy mission.  I want the Berlin police fully briefed and --  -- get this out to all the agencies.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: It's hard to swallow.  The confusion -- the amnesia -- but he keeps on killing? It's more calculated than sick.  What about Nicky? She's the last one to see Bourne in Paris. She's the one he asks for. They disappear...

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: So what's he doing? You believe him?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: There are no answers. There's either Jason Bourne alive or Jason Bourne dead. And I for one would prefer the latter. And what about her?  You just send her out to this lunatic with no protection?

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: Don't you want answers?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: My ass he does. You're playing with fire Pamela. Marshall said nail him to the wall. I don't know how you interpreted that but I don't think he meant repatriate him.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: Hold on -- he said he wants to come in.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Call a Mayday into Berlin station. We need snipers DOD whatever they got. Snipers?

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: And you do? From the moment he left Treadstone he has killed and eluded every person that you sent to find him...

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: You don't know what you're getting into here.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: I've already got a team there. I doubt Bourne's in Naples to settle down and raise a family.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Berlin!

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: So what's your theory?  Conklin's reaching out from the grave to protect his good name?  The man is dead.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: What's definitive is that I just lost two people in Berlin!

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Conklin might've been a nut but he wasn't a mole. You have me his calendar for a couple of days I'll prove he killed Lincoln.  This is supposed to be definitive?

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: May I finish?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: We were throwing money at him. Throwing it at him and asking him to keep it dark.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: Excuse me.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Do you know what his budget was?

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: ...At the time of his death Conklin was sitting on a personal account in the amount of seven-hundred and sixty thousand dollars.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: ...this is Conklin's computer.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: ...Ivan Mevedev -- senior financial manager -- worked for one of the new Russian petroleum companies Pecos Oil. He claimed to know where the money landed. We believe this could have only happened with help from someone inside the Agency... This...

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: I think I do. We had a deal going down in Berlin last week. During the buy both our Field Agent and the seller were killed. We pulled a fingerprint from a timing charge that didn't go off.  They were killed by Jason Bourne.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Dead in a ditch? Drunk in a bar in Mogadishu? Who knows?

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: And Bourne? Where's he now?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: I've given thirty years and two marriages to this agency. I've shoveled shit on four continents. I'm due to retire next year and believe me I need my pension but if you think I'm gonna sit here and let you dangle me with this you can go to hell. Marshall too.  It had to be done.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: So you had Conklin killed.  I mean if we're cutting the crap...

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: What happened? Jason Bourne happened.  You've got the files? Then let's cut the crap. It went wrong. Conklin had these guys wound so tight they were bound to snap. Bourne was his number one -- guy went out to work screwed the op and never came back. Conklin couldn't fix it couldn't find Bourne couldn't adjust. It all went sideways. Finally there were no options left.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: I want to know what happened.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: What are you after Pam? You want to fry me? You want my desk? Is that it?

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: Let's talk about Conklin.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: He does. I've been down to the archives. I have the files Ward.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: To know about it?  It was a kill squad. Black on black. Closed down two years ago. Nobody wants to know about Treadstone. Not around here.  You better take this back to Marty and make sure he knows what you're doing.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: I want to know about Treadstone.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: And what are we looking for?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: With all due respect Pam I think you might've wandered a little past your pay-grade.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: That's not gonna fly.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Never heard of it.

title: m39
speaker: PAMELA
speech: Treadstone.

title: m39
speaker: ZORN
speech: Okay...

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Show me again...

title: m39
speaker: ZORN
speech: Nobody. You.  I had to tell you right?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Who else knows about this?

title: m39
speaker: ZORN
speech: Including Landy...  She had access to the archives.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Lots of people...

title: m39
speaker: ZORN
speech: Something's been going on here in Europe. And it's still going on. Post Conklin. Who's been in Berlin?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Keep going...

title: m39
speaker: ZORN
speech: Okay. What if someone decided to cover their tracks by blaming Conklin and Bourne. What if Bourne didn't have anything to do with this?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Jesus...

title: m39
speaker: ZORN
speech: Is it a slam dunk? No but...

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: It was staged?

title: m39
speaker: ZORN
speech: There were two charges they were supposed to go off simultaneously. The second one the one that didn't go off was down here...  First of all this is nothing it's a sub-line for the breaker above. Second why put the charge all the way down here? If you're good enough to get in here and handle the gear you're good enough to know you don't need this.  Bourne would know.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: And?

title: m39
speaker: ZORN
speech: You put a four-gam Kel on here and it's gonna take out power to the building. You know that. What you can't know is if it's gonna blow the room with it.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: What do you have Danny?

title: m39
speaker: ZORN
speech: I did my box work but I wanted to show you before I showed Landy. I came out here last night because none of this was making any sense. I mean I'm with you on this Conklin was a nut but a traitor? I just can't get there.

title: m39
speaker: ZORN
speech: The sooner the better.

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: She say what time I should call?

title: m39
speaker: ABBOTT
speech: Thanks.

title: m39
speaker: ZORN
speech: Sir...

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I'm sorry.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: Is this really happening?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I have to go now.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: No.  Because you don't want to know how it feels.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: Because you're afraid!

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I can't let you do that either.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: I should kill you... if it's true you should die... I should kill you now!

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Look at me.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: YOU'RE A LIAR!

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: You know I'm not.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: You're a liar.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: It doesn't matter. Your life is hard enough.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I don't want you to forgive me.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: How... how can... how can you be here and say this?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: They loved you.  And I killed them.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: You killed them.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: It was my job. My first time. Your father was supposed to be alone. But then your mother she came out of nowhere...  I had to change my plan.  You understand me?  You don't have to live like that anymore. Thinking that.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I killed them.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: Then what?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: That's not what happened to your parents.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: Yes...

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: It changes things. That knowledge. Doesn't it?

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: What?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I would want to know.  I would want to know that my mother didn't kill my father. I would want to know that she didn't kill herself.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: No I do.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: No. It's because you don't know how they died.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: It's nothing. It's just a picture.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: It's nice.  Does this picture mean anything to you?  Hmm?

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: Okay.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Of all the people in the world you're the only one I have anything to offer.  That's why I came here.

title: m39
speaker: IRENA
speech: I speak English.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Sit. Can you...  [The chair. Have the chair.]

speech: -- take the back -- get another car --

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: -- what? --

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: -- my coat -- but we should --

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: -- car keys?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: How long? How long do I have --

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: I'm sorry.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: You called it in?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I did.

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: She really did that? Told you not to kill me?  I had a woman once. But after a while what do you talk about? I mean for us. The work. You can't tell them who you are...

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: I don't know! Why would I lie?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: What's going on in Berlin?

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: I don't know who that is.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Pamela Landy?

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: A voice. A voice from the States. Someone new.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Who sent you to Greece?

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: I don't know.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: You're lying. If it's over why are they after me?

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: Shot dead in Paris. Dead the night you walked out.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Try again.

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: He's dead.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Conklin.

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: What do you want?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: She wouldn't let me.  She's the only reason you're alive.

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: So why didn't you kill me then?

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: I like it here.  Last time I saw you was Greece. You had a good spot.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: You still should've moved.

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: Sorry. Old habits.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Front. Use your teeth.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Drop it.

title: m39
speaker: JARDA
speech: Felt a little light.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I emptied it.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: Jason. You know exactly what to do. That is your mission now.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: God I miss you. I don't know what to do without you.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I only dream about people who are dead.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: You do?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I know it's a dream.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: It might have.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: It wouldn't have changed the way you feel.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I did.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: But you found another choice.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I wanted to kill him.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Tell me later.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: I love you too.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: There's no choice.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: Jason please don't do this...it won't ever be over like this.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I warned them Marie. I told them to leave us alone.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: There must be another way!

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: If he crosses the bridge it is.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: What if it's not who you think it is?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I'm going to bail on the other side and wait. This bridge is the only way he can follow.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: Where are you going?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: You keep going to the shack. I'll meet you there in an hour.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: -- hang on --

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: -- yeah -- one guy -- I don't think he was ready --

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: -- it's just him? --

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: -- not yet --

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: Jesus! --  -- is he back there? --

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: -- make the left -- toward the bridge --

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: -- where? -

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Switch! You drive!

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: What?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: You drive.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: -- there's places -- we can't afford to be wrong!

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: -- where's left to go? --

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Look we clear out we get to the shack we get safe. We hang there awhile. I'll come back. I'll check it out. But right now we can't --

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: I don't want to move again... I like it here.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: We can't wait to be sure.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: ...but you're not -- you're not sure...

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Back there -- at the corner -- Hyundai -- silver --

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: Where --

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: No. Not this. This is real.  And he's right there...

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: That's crazy.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: It's wrong. Guy with a rental car and hundred dollar sneakers sleeps in a tent?

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: So...

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: He was at the campground yesterday.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: But you're sure?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: We pushed it. We got lazy.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: But we were so careful.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: The Telegraph office.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: No... How?

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: One day it will be different. It just takes time.  We'll make new memories. You and me.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: But it ends up the same.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: You are better. And I think it's not memories at all. It's just a dream you keep having over and over.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I should be better by now.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: Sleep. Sleep now.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: I don't mean that. I worry when you try to ignore it.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: It's just a nightmare.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: I worry when you get like this.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I'm trying Marie Okay?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I do remember something good. All the time. I remember you.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: We write them down because sooner or later you're going to remember something good.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: -- it's always bad and it's never anything but bits and pieces anyway!  You ever think that maybe it's just making it worse? You don't wonder that?

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: -- it hasn't been two years --

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Two years we're scribbling in a notebook --

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: You're sure?  We should still -- we should write it down.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: No. There's nothing new.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: I'll get the book.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Conklin up front.

title: m39
speaker: MARIE
speech: Where were you Jason? In the car.

speech: ...it's not in the file... I swear... I know your file... your first job was Geneva!... I swear to God you never worked here!...

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I was here!

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: No... Jason... please...

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: You never worked Berlin...

speaker: BOURNE
speech: That's a lie!

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: Your first assignment was Geneva.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: My first job.

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: No. You never worked Berlin.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: For Treadstone. In Berlin. You know my file. I did a job here. When?

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: What do you mean?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: So when was I here?

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: He closed down Treadstone -- he took care of me after Paris...

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Abbott?

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: Please -- I'm only here because of Paris -- because they can't figure out what you're doing -- I'm here because of Abbott --

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Why are you here then?

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: Conklin! Stuff on Conklin!

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: What was Landy buying? What kind of files?  WHAT WAS SHE BUYING?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I left a fingerprint! You fucking people.

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: You left a print! There was Kel that didn't go off! There was a partial print they tracked it back to Treadstone! They know it's you!

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I killed him???

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: And you got to him before we could.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Last week? When?

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: It was Pamela Landy's op. The guy was going to sell-out a mole or something. I haven't been debriefed on exactly what it was.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: A Russian?

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: Last week an Agency field officer went to make a buy from a Russian national.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Say it.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: I want to hear it from you.

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: What is this a game?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: How do they know that? How can they know any of that?

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: They know!  They know you were here. They know you killed these two guys. They know you and Conklin had something on the side. They don't know what it is but they know!

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Why is she trying to kill me?

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: IS SHE RUNNING TREADSTONE?

title: m39
speaker: NICKY
speech: You hear me? I believed you.

title: m39
speaker: BOURNE
speech: Who is Pamela Landy?
